HEADWORD: Motorman
<hw>Mo"tor*man</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A man
who controls a motor.</def> <mark>[archaic]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>an operator of a motor vehicle, especially of a
streetcar or subway train.</def> ⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Motormouth</ent>⟦br⟧
